This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of semantic part detection in images. Additionally, the use of a new network module (OffsetNet) to predict part locations within objects suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision research. 

The paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves the use of object information and modeling expected relative locations of parts, which could be seen as a form of reasoning or knowledge representation. 

The machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper involves training a model to detect semantic parts using various cues. 

The natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve some text analysis or processing of natural language descriptions of objects and their parts. 

Finally, the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with analyzing images and detecting semantic parts within them, which could be considered a form of multimedia analysis.
